<subSubSection box="[199,1422,726,751]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,546,1254]" box="[199,1422,726,751]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,727,751]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Etymology.</emphasis>
Latin adjective 
<taxonomicName box="[515,602,726,750]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Ilargus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foliosus">
<emphasis box="[515,602,726,750]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">foliosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(leafy), referring to the leaf-like marking on the dorsum of the abdomen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,546,1254]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,762,787]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[458,689,763,787]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Ilargus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrocornis">
<emphasis box="[458,689,763,787]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Ilargus macrocornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the color and marking patterns, and the presence of guanine deposit in the eye area (
<figureCitation box="[416,547,798,822]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 59" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1665,1688]" captionTargetBox="[160,1420,193,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,193,1645]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 59. Ilargus foliosus sp. nov. 53 male holotype, dorsal view; 54 female paratype, dorsal view; 55 male left palp, ventral view; 56 male left palp, retrolateral view; 57 female left chelicera, back view; 58 epigynum, ventral view; 59 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 53 – 54, 0.5 mm; 55 – 59, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209893/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Figs 
<number box="[473,547,798,822]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="53.5" valueMax="54.0" valueMin="53.0">53–54</number>
</figureCitation>
), but differs in the absence of a spur on the front surface of the male chelicera.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,546,1254]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,834,859]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[351,408,835,859]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Male</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[424,526,834,858]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">holotype</typeStatus>
, UBC-SEM AR00148). Carapace length 
<number box="[991,1029,834,858]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1.7">1.7</number>
; abdomen length 
<number box="[1229,1267,834,858]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1.7">1.7</number>
. Chelicera: red brown. Palp (
<figureCitation box="[304,437,870,894]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 59" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1665,1688]" captionTargetBox="[160,1420,193,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,193,1645]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 59. Ilargus foliosus sp. nov. 53 male holotype, dorsal view; 54 female paratype, dorsal view; 55 male left palp, ventral view; 56 male left palp, retrolateral view; 57 female left chelicera, back view; 58 epigynum, ventral view; 59 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 53 – 54, 0.5 mm; 55 – 59, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209893/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Figs 
<number box="[362,437,870,894]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="55.5" valueMax="56.0" valueMin="55.0">55–56</number>
</figureCitation>
): tibia and cymbium dark brown, other segments cream. Embolus long with a relatively wide spiral; proximal tegular lobe large; retrolateral sperm duct loop occupying more than half of bulb width; retrolateral tibial apophysis finger-like; ventral tibial bump absent. Measurements of legs: I 
<number box="[1193,1230,942,966]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="3.3">3.3</number>
, II 
<number box="[1270,1308,942,966]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2.9">2.9</number>
, III 
<number box="[1356,1393,942,966]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="3.4">3.4</number>
, IV 
<number box="[151,189,978,1002]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="3.6">3.6</number>
. Color in alcohol (
<figureCitation box="[398,483,978,1002]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 59" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1665,1688]" captionTargetBox="[160,1420,193,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,193,1645]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 59. Ilargus foliosus sp. nov. 53 male holotype, dorsal view; 54 female paratype, dorsal view; 55 male left palp, ventral view; 56 male left palp, retrolateral view; 57 female left chelicera, back view; 58 epigynum, ventral view; 59 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 53 – 54, 0.5 mm; 55 – 59, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209893/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig. 
<number box="[451,483,978,1002]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="53.0">53</number>
</figureCitation>
): carapace dark brown, eye area with guanine deposit, behind eye area with a medial and two marginal yellowish stripes; abdomen dark brown, with many silvery white speckles and a large leaf-like mark medially; legs yellowish to dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,546,1254]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis box="[199,283,1086,1110]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Female</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[299,400,1086,1110]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">paratype</typeStatus>
, UBC-SEM AR00149). Carapace length 
<number box="[873,911,1086,1110]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1.4">1.4</number>
; abdomen length 
<number box="[1115,1153,1086,1110]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1.8">1.8</number>
. Chelicera (
<figureCitation box="[1291,1378,1086,1110]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 59" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1665,1688]" captionTargetBox="[160,1420,193,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,193,1645]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 59. Ilargus foliosus sp. nov. 53 male holotype, dorsal view; 54 female paratype, dorsal view; 55 male left palp, ventral view; 56 male left palp, retrolateral view; 57 female left chelicera, back view; 58 epigynum, ventral view; 59 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 53 – 54, 0.5 mm; 55 – 59, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209893/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig. 
<number box="[1346,1378,1086,1110]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="57.0">57</number>
</figureCitation>
): red brown. Measurements of legs: I 
<number box="[528,565,1122,1146]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2.4">2.4</number>
, II 
<number box="[609,647,1122,1146]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2.2">2.2</number>
, III 
<number box="[699,736,1122,1146]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2.6">2.6</number>
, IV 
<number box="[791,830,1122,1146]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="3.2">3.2</number>
. Epigynum (
<figureCitation box="[978,1066,1122,1146]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 59" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1665,1688]" captionTargetBox="[160,1420,193,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,193,1645]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 59. Ilargus foliosus sp. nov. 53 male holotype, dorsal view; 54 female paratype, dorsal view; 55 male left palp, ventral view; 56 male left palp, retrolateral view; 57 female left chelicera, back view; 58 epigynum, ventral view; 59 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 53 – 54, 0.5 mm; 55 – 59, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209893/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig. 
<number box="[1034,1066,1122,1146]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="58.0">58</number>
</figureCitation>
): window large; median septum relatively narrow; opening to copulatory duct at each side of median septum anteriorly. Vulva (
<figureCitation box="[1212,1296,1158,1182]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 59" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1665,1688]" captionTargetBox="[160,1420,193,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,193,1645]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 59. Ilargus foliosus sp. nov. 53 male holotype, dorsal view; 54 female paratype, dorsal view; 55 male left palp, ventral view; 56 male left palp, retrolateral view; 57 female left chelicera, back view; 58 epigynum, ventral view; 59 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 53 – 54, 0.5 mm; 55 – 59, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209893/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig. 
<number box="[1264,1296,1158,1182]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="59.0">59</number>
</figureCitation>
): copulatory duct slightly convoluted; spermatheca almost stomach-shaped. Color in alcohol (
<figureCitation box="[1069,1154,1194,1218]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 59" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1665,1688]" captionTargetBox="[160,1420,193,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,193,1645]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 59. Ilargus foliosus sp. nov. 53 male holotype, dorsal view; 54 female paratype, dorsal view; 55 male left palp, ventral view; 56 male left palp, retrolateral view; 57 female left chelicera, back view; 58 epigynum, ventral view; 59 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 53 – 54, 0.5 mm; 55 – 59, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209893/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig. 
<number box="[1122,1154,1194,1218]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="54.0">54</number>
</figureCitation>
): similar to that of male, but first two pairs of legs lighter in color than those of male.
</paragraph>
